E-3 PROVISIONAL NOTE. The CC-BY-4.0 grant applies to FreeNIC's own compilation,
curation, derivation, and metadata. Individual upstream sources carry their own
terms — most are US Government / regulatory public-domain works (FFIEC, FDIC,
Federal Reserve, OCC, FRED, NCUA, SEC), but a few academic/derived sources
(Correia-Luck-Verner "Failing Banks"; finhist / Harvard Dataverse DOI
10.7910/DVN/Q22XR1; the bank-data-dictionary) require citation and are governed
by their source terms for the source data itself. See DATA_LICENSE.md and
Outputs/PROVENANCE.csv for the per-table, per-era source terms and required
citations. Where upstream data terms and CC-BY-4.0 could appear to conflict, the
upstream terms govern that source's data only. This E-3 licensing note is
PROVISIONAL pending final per-source clearance review.

FreeNIC's source CODE remains under the MIT License (see the repository LICENSE).
